						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up on the path near the mosque.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Sadāśiva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1480, Kāḷayukti Āśvija śu. 7, Friday</hi> corresponding to 1558 A.D., September 19. However, the weekday is not Friday, but it is Monday.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of the money called Vīramushṭi-pannu of the villages in Cheyyēṭi-sīma made for the merit of the <hi rend="italic">Siddhabikshā-vṛitti-Ayya</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Vīramushṭis</hi> by some <hi rend="italic">Seṭṭi.</hi> It also mentions the <hi rend="italic">Ayyāvali</hi> community.</p>						

						</summary>
